<emphasis id="B911EAA6FF9DFF842FA6E80FA130FDA6" bold="true" box="[192,376,545,570]" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">
<typeStatus id="54DE8816FF9DFF842FA6E80FA14DFDA5" box="[192,261,546,570]" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">Type</typeStatus>
species.
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C654D37FF9DFF842E19E80FA35BFDA5" authority="Leconte 1876" authorityName="Leconte" authorityYear="1876" box="[383,787,546,570]" class="Insecta" family="Anthribidae" genus="Eusphyrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="walshii">
<emphasis id="B911EAA6FF9DFF842E19E80FA22EFDA5" box="[383,614,546,570]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">Eusphyrus walshii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFF44B45FF9DFF842D0BE80FA35BFDA5" author="LeConte, J. L." box="[621,787,546,570]" pageId="27" pageNumber="26" pagination="1 - 455" refId="ref19586" refString="LeConte, J. L. 1876. p. l 1 - 25. In: J. L. LeConte and G. H. Horn (eds.). The Rhynchophora of America, north of Mexico. Proceedings of the American Philosophical Society 15: 1 - 455." type="journal article" year="1876">Leconte 1876</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, by monotypy.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDA36B4FF9DFF842FA6E84CA35BFD45" blockId="27.[192,1440,609,730]" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis id="B911EAA6FF9DFF842FA6E84CA18AFDE6" bold="true" box="[192,450,609,633]" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">Generic diagnosis.</emphasis>
Species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C654D37FF9DFF842D36E84FA29CFDE5" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1876" box="[592,724,610,634]" class="Insecta" family="Anthribidae" genus="Eusphyrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B911EAA6FF9DFF842D36E84FA29CFDE5" box="[592,724,610,634]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">Eusphyrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very similar to species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C654D37FF9DFF842B5BE84FA4FAFDE6" box="[1085,1202,610,633]" class="Insecta" family="Anthribidae" genus="Ormiscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B911EAA6FF9DFF842B5BE84FA4FAFDE6" box="[1085,1202,610,633]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">Ormiscus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but can be distinguished by the basal or sub-basal transverse pronotal carina that is capable of contacting the elytral base. These genera can also be confused with species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C654D37FF9DFF842C02E88FA45EFD25" authorityName="Wollaston" authorityYear="1861" box="[868,1046,674,698]" class="Insecta" family="Anthribidae" genus="Trigonorhinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B911EAA6FF9DFF842C02E88FA45EFD25" box="[868,1046,674,698]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">Trigonorhinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but can be distinguished by the quadrate rostrum that does not narrow apically.
</paragraph>
